.TH "HPC\-COMPOSE\-NOTEBOOK\-PROMOTE" "1" "" "hpc\-compose 0.2.3" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
hpc\-compose\-notebook\-promote \- Promote a tracked notebook session into a batch compose spec
.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
hpc\-compose notebook promote [OPTIONS] <NOTEBOOK.ipynb>
.fi
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
Read a tracked notebook session record and write a static compose YAML spec that runs the notebook through Papermill. This is an authoring\-only command: it does not contact Slurm, run preflight or prepare, or execute Papermill.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fINOTEBOOK.ipynb\fR
Notebook to execute in batch.
.TP
\fB--record\fR \fIPATH\fR
Tracked notebook record to read; defaults to .hpc\-compose/latest\-notebook.json.
.TP
\fB--output\fR \fIPATH\fR
Compose YAML output path; defaults to <notebook\-stem>.promoted.yaml.
.TP
\fB--force\fR
Overwrite the output file if it already exists.
.TP
\fB--image\fR \fIIMAGE\fR
Container image to use when the tracked record has no recoverable image.
.TP
\fB--volume\fR \fIHOST:CONTAINER\fR
Additional runtime mount to include in the promoted service.
.TP
\fB--working\-dir\fR \fIPATH\fR
Container working directory.
.TP
\fB--requirements\fR \fIPATH\fR
requirements.txt to mount and install during x\-runtime.prepare.
.TP
\fB--prepare\-command\fR \fICMD\fR
Additional x\-runtime.prepare command; may be passed multiple times.
.TP
\fB--param\fR \fINAME=DEFAULT\fR
Papermill parameter exposed via ${NAME:\-DEFAULT}; may be passed multiple times.
.TP
\fB--color\fR \fIWHEN\fR
Controls colored output. Default: auto. Possible values: auto, always, never.
.TP
\fB--quiet\fR
Suppress progress indicators and non\-essential labels.
.TP
\fB-v\fR, \fB--verbose\fR
Increase diagnostic verbosity; repeat for debug\-level logs.
.TP
\fB--debug\fR
Enable debug\-level diagnostics (equivalent to \-vv unless RUST_LOG is set).
.TP
\fB--profile\fR \fINAME\fR
Profile name to load from .hpc\-compose/settings.toml.
.TP
\fB--settings\-file\fR \fIPATH\fR
Explicit settings file path; defaults to upward search for .hpc\-compose/settings.toml.
.TP
\fB--offline\fR
Forbid SSH, remote delegation, Slurm scheduler contact, submissions, allocations, and cancels.
.TP
\fB-h\fR, \fB--help\fR
Print help (see a summary with '\-h').
